y** | `certify` (built from `cmd\/certify\/`) |\n| **Test command** | `go test .\/... -count=1` |\n| **Build command** | `go build -o build\/bin\/certify .\/cmd\/certify\/` |\n\n### Target Files (what the issue says vs. what exists)\n\nThe issue names `internal\/report\/report.go` as the target file — **this file does not exist**. The report card generation is distributed across these files, all in `internal\/report\/`:\n\n| File | What it does | Must change? |\n|------|-------------|--------------|\n| **`card.go`** | `GenerateCard()` — computes overall GPA, grade distribution, pass rate, language breakdown; `FormatCardText()` and `FormatCardMarkdown()` — render the report card | **YES** — core change |\n| **`full.go`** | `GenerateFullReport()` wraps `GenerateCard()`; `buildLanguageDetail()` — computes per-language stats | **YES** — `buildLanguageDetail` must exclude unsupported |\n| **`badge.go`** | `GenerateBadge()` — reads `Card` for badge message and color | **YES** — badge message must use supported-only counts |\n| **`health.go`** | `Health()` — computes AverageScore, PassRate, status counts | **YES** — must exclude unsupported units |\n| **`detailed.go`** | `Detailed()` — wraps `Health()`; `computeDimensionAverages()`, `computeLanguageBreakdowns()` | **YES** — must exclude unsupported units |\n| **`report_tree.go`** | `BuildPackageSummaries()`, `GenerateReportTree()` — site\/report tree | **YES** — package summaries should exclude unsupported |\n| **`site.go`** | `GenerateSite()` — HTML site generation | Likely needs update |\n\n### How Unsupported Languages Work Today\n\n1. **Discovery**: `internal\/discovery\/generic.go` maps ~25 file extensions to language identifiers via `certifiableExts`. All are discovered as file-level units.\n\n2. **Analyzers registered** (in `internal\/analysis\/` via `init()` functions):\n   - `go` → `GoAnalyzer` (go_analyzer.go)\n   - `ts`, `js` → `TSAnalyzer` (ts_analyzer.go)\n   - `py` → `PythonAnalyzer` (python_analyzer.go)\n   - `rs` → `RustAnalyzer` (rust_analyzer.go)\n\n3. **Unsupported languages** (in `certifiableExts` but NO analyzer): `rb`, `java`, `kt`, `sh`, `bash`, `c`, `cpp`, `cs`, `swift`, `php`, `elixir`, `erlang`, `scala`, `lua`, `r`, `zig`, `sql`, `proto`\n\n4. **Pipeline** (`internal\/engine\/certifier.go`:`collectStructuralEvidence`): When `analysis.ForLanguage(lang)` returns `nil` and the file isn't Go, structural evidence is simply not added. But the unit still gets: file-level code metrics, git history, policy evaluation → a **fabricated grade** based on very limited evidence.\n\n5. **No `Unsupported` field exists** on `domain.CertificationRecord`. The determination must happen at report-generation time.\n\n### Approach Decision (recorded)\n\n**Determine unsupported at report-generation time** by calling `analysis.ForLanguage(lang) == nil`. The report package will import `analysis` and use the existing registry. This respects the non-goal of not changing `scorer.go` or any engine code.\n\n### Specific Changes Required\n\n#### 1. `Card` struct (`card.go`) — new fields needed:\n\n```go\n\/\/ Added to Card struct:\nUnsupportedUnits     int      \/\/ count of units in unsupported languages\nUnsupportedLanguages []string \/\/ distinct unsupported language names\nSupportedUnits       int      \/\/ denominator for aggregate stats\n```\n\n#### 2. `GenerateCard()` (`card.go`) — partition logic:\n\nAfter iterating records, the function must:\n- Partition records into supported (`analysis.ForLanguage(r.UnitID.Language()) != nil`) vs unsupported\n- Compute `OverallScore` only from supported units\n- Compute `GradeDistribution` only from supported units\n- Compute `PassRate` only from supported units  \n- Compute `Languages` only from supported units\n- Track `UnsupportedUnits` count and distinct `UnsupportedLanguages` names\n- Set `SupportedUnits` as the denominator\n\n#### 3. `FormatCardText()` and `FormatCardMarkdown()` (`card.go`) — banner:\n\nAdd a banner section when `c.UnsupportedUnits > 0`:\n```\n⚠️ 3 units in unsupported languages (swift, shell, cpp) — not analyzed.\n   Scores for these units are withheld.\n```\n\nAnd in the aggregate stats:\n```\nBased on 42 analyzable units; 3 units skipped.\n```\n\n#### 4. `GenerateBadge()` (`badge.go`):\n\nChange `badgeMessage()` to use `c.SupportedUnits` instead of `c.TotalUnits` for the unit count in the badge.\n\n#### 5. `Health()` (`health.go`):\n\nExclude unsupported units from `TotalUnits`, `AverageScore`, `PassRate`, and all status counts.\n\n#### 6. `Detailed()` \/ `computeDimensionAverages()` \/ `computeLanguageBreakdowns()` (`detailed.go`):\n\nAll must skip unsupported units.\n\n#### 7. `buildLanguageDetail()` (`full.go`):\n\nOnly include supported languages.\n\n#### 8. `BuildPackageSummaries()` (`report_tree.go`):\n\nSkip unsupported units.\n\n### Tests That Must Pass\n\nAll existing tests in `internal\/report\/*_test.go`:\n- `card_test.go` — 6 tests\n- `full_test.go` — 8 tests  \n- `badge_test.go` — 5 tests\n- `detailed_test.go` — 7 tests\n- `health_test.go`\n- `site_test.go`\n- `report_tree_test.go`\n\nThese tests all use `go` and `ts` as languages — both are supported — so they should pass **as-is** after changes since unsupported filtering won't affect supported-language records. New tests should be added for the unsupported case.\n\n### Non-goals (confirmed)\n\n- `internal\/engine\/scorer.go` — do NOT touch\n- No `language_tiers.go` file exists anywhere in the repo\n- `cmd\/certify\/init_cmd.go` — do NOT touch\n- Visual design of report card beyond the banner — no other formatting changes\n\n### Verification\n\n```bash\ngo test .\/... -count=1\n```\n\nSpecifically, the report package tests must pass. The `internal\/analysis` package need not be changed — the report package will import it to call `ForLanguage()`.","outcome":{"note":{}},"at":805829012.042172,"id":"27-564"}
